  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-cou1-not-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Not accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CFD hemolysis prediction for CPB Class II device, MRL 2) results in a Not-Accepted decision based on the following structured evidence: (1) Discretization error [achievedLevel 1 < requiredLevel 2]: GCI of 12.4% for the primary QOI exceeds the 5% threshold; non-monotonic mesh convergence in near-wall shear stress indicates the spatial resolution is insufficient to reliably capture hemolysis-relevant flow features. (2) Test conditions [achievedLevel 1 < requiredLevel 2]: The validation experimental envelope does not cover the full range of clinical CPB operating conditions; two of five target operating points are outside the characterized test space, and physiologically relevant variability in hematocrit and temperature was not represented. (3) Output comparison [achievedLevel 1 < requiredLevel 2]: Mean absolute prediction error of 28% relative to experimental measurements is inconsistent with the precision required to evaluate the RH < 1 acceptance criterion with adequate confidence. Systematic over-prediction at low-shear operating points indicates a model form deficiency not captured by random uncertainty alone. (4) Relevance of validation activities to COU [achievedLevel 1 < requiredLevel 2]: All validation evidence pertains to the nominal FDA pump geometry; no validation data support extrapolation to the dimensional variants that constitute the actual COU (worst-case hemolysis across component dimension variations). (5) Model form [achievedLevel 1 < requiredLevel 2]: The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis correlation exhibits up to 35% QOI variation relative to alternative formulations at low-shear conditions; formal model-form uncertainty has not been quantified or incorporated into prediction intervals. (6) Equivalency of input parameters [achievedLevel 1 < requiredLevel 2]: Simulation boundary conditions for two corner-case operating points fall outside the validated Reynolds number range of the turbulence model, and equivalency has not been demonstrated for these conditions. Six of thirteen assessed factors achieve levels below their required levels. The combined effect of uncontrolled discretization error, insufficient validation coverage, large output comparison error, and unquantified model-form uncertainty renders the model predictions insufficiently credible for regulatory submission in support of the intended COU. The assessment team recommends: (a) mesh refinement to achieve GCI < 5% for NIH, (b) expanded experimental validation covering dimensional variants and the full clinical operating envelope, (c) formal model-form uncertainty quantification comparing at least three hemolysis correlation formulations, and (d) re-assessment prior to resubmission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
